----------------Git------------------
----------------Basic And Advance----
 --- Install ---
  sudo apt-get install git
--- Check Git Version -----
  git --version or git -v
------Create new Directory -----
  mkdir Git-practice
------ go to the Git-practice --
  cd Git-practice
 -- Then run the Command --
   git init # git init initializes a new Git repository by creating a .git directory to track project changes.
   -- Create a file like this --
   echo "Hello I am anuj Singh" > anuj.txt
   ls #this commamd shows how many files present in this directory.
----- Configure Your Identity ---
  git config --global user.name "Anuj" # "please write your github username".
git config --global user.email "anuj@example.com"
---- for checking the Config ----
 git config --global --list



---- For checking Status ----
  git status

---- For adding the File into staging area ----
  git add  anuj.txt
------- For Commit Changes ----
  git commit -m " 1st commit" # "-m ka use commit message directly command line se dene ke liye hota hai."
---------- Connect to Remote Repository (GitHub) ---------
 Go to the Github account Create one Repo in your account.
 Then come to the terminal
 git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo-name.git # " In this command you use your link repo. 
  ---- For verify ---
  git remote -v
--------- Push Code to GitHub -----
 git push -u origin main



----------------- Summary Or Daily Git Workflow (MOST USED) ----------
git pull
git status
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git push



 ----------------- Intermediate --------------------------



 ---------- For creating Branch ------

   git branch Dev  Or # "here Dev is branch creating"
 
 --------------- For  checking the branch -------
 git branch
 ---------- Branch switch karna -----
 git checkout Master Or git switch Master # " if you want to switch branch Dev to master you can this command"

git checkout -b testing # "This command create branch and also switch to that Branch"

----- Golden Rule * Kaam karne se pehle branch check karo -- please check the branch whenever you start working.
------------ For History clean ----------------
git checkout Dev
git rebase master

-------- Copy remote repo to local system ------
git clone https://github.com/user/project.git -- # you use your link --"


